ğŸ§© Relationship to Mainnet

Testnets run the same Ethereum protocol and EVM (Ethereum Virtual Machine) as the mainnet.

However, they have different chain IDs, different native tokens, and separate states â€” meaning balances, contracts, and transactions on a testnet do not exist on mainnet.

They are completely isolated networks â€” but designed to simulate mainnet behavior for development and testing.

