ğŸª™ 2. Tokens live inside Ethereum as smart contracts

A token (like USDT, DAI, SHIB, LINK, etc.) is just a smart contract deployed on Ethereum.

These contracts follow standard interfaces like:

ERC-20 â†’ for fungible tokens (currencies, governance tokens)

ERC-721 â†’ for NFTs

ERC-1155 â†’ for mixed-type assets (both fungible & non-fungible)

Each token contract defines:

How many tokens exist

Who owns what

How transfers work

Example:
When you â€œsendâ€ 10 USDT to someone, the USDT smart contract updates its internal balance records â€” no new blockchain or coin is created.

